    • Enum Constant Detail

      • ZK_SERVERS

        public static final PropertyNames ZK_SERVERS
        Specifies the ZooKeeper connection string in the form hostname:port where host and port are the host and port of a ZooKeeper server. To allow connecting through other ZooKeeper nodes when that ZooKeeper machine is down you can also specify multiple hosts in the form hostname1:port1,hostname2:port2,hostname3:port3.

        Property Name: zookeeper.connect

        Default Value: zookeeper-1:2181,zookeeper-2:2181,zookeeper-3:2181

      • ZK_SESSION_TIMEOUT_MS

        public static final PropertyNames ZK_SESSION_TIMEOUT_MS
        ZooKeeper session timeout. If the Zookeeper connection fails to heartbeat to ZooKeeper for this period of time it is considered dead.

        Property Name: zookeeper.session.timeout.ms

        Default Value: 8000

      • ZK_CONNECTION_TIMEOUT_MS

        public static final PropertyNames ZK_CONNECTION_TIMEOUT_MS
        The max time that Zookeeper client waits while establishing a connection to zookeeper ensemble.

        Property Name: zookeeper.connection.timeout.ms

        Default Value: 5000

      • ZK_NODE_POLL_DELAY_TIME_MS

        public static final PropertyNames ZK_NODE_POLL_DELAY_TIME_MS
        Zookeeper node polling delay. It is the delay time in ms between the termination of one Zookeeper node polling and the commencement of the next.

        Property Name: zookeeper.node.poll.delay.time.ms

        Default Value: 1000

      • ZK_NODE_POLL_INITIAL_DELAY_TIME_MS

        public static final PropertyNames ZK_NODE_POLL_INITIAL_DELAY_TIME_MS
        Zookeeper node polling initial delay It is the time in ms to delay first Zookeeper node polling

        Property Name: zookeeper.node.poll.initial.delay.time.ms

        Default Value: 0
